description:
Tales of Lyla is an epic high fantasy comic, following the adventures of Van Gaia, a young and brave sorcerer in training from the kingdom of Unmond, with a dream to become one of his kingdom's royal sages and learn more about his secret family history. And Pendle Windle, a hot headed teenage witch from the cursed, witch infested swamplands that dabbles with dark magic as her specialty.

Pendle joins Van's crusade in order to learn more about the world outside of the swamplands she was raised in and prove to the world that witches can be a lot more than just a source of dread. Van’s greatest insecurity stems from the fact that due to a general lack of support in his fascination with the mystical arts, he never found his specialty in the field. Van’s skills are scattered and he is forced to use a combination of wits and skill, while Pendle is a trigger happy over confident sorceress who is proud in relying on her magical skills.

On their journey Van and Pendle will make their way through the mysterious world of Lyla, solving cases that involve or result from supernatural causes. They will make new friends, new enemies and will uncover an endless array of magical mysteries. But Van and Pendle’s personal quest slowly tangles them deep in a secret war that threatens to shake their entire reality to its core and reveal secrets about the world of Lyla that should have stayed buried deep within its history.
name: Tales of Lyla

description:
English digital edition.

A gripping supernatural thriller of biblical proportions...quite literally. When detective Jason Ash arrives on the scene of a particularly strange murder in the suburbs of New Orleans, little does he know that he is about to take on the case of a lifetime. As dead people begin to come back to life, revealing that they hail from a realm where angels fight for power, it becomes clear that an epic battle between good and evil is at play, one threatening the very future of humanity. Written by screenwriter Thomas Fenton and drawn by Jamal Igle (DC's Supergirl, Teen Titans: Titans of Tomorrow ) and Steven Cummings.
name: Dominion

description:
English digital edition.

An old-fashioned yet truly original noir tale set in 1920s New York where an unlikely pair of detectives pursue a mysterious killer. Freshly returned from WWI, ex-detective John Lord is convinced to reactivate a special investigative agency known as the UPIs to probe the grisly death of its founder. As John is joined by Clara, an opinionated psychology student, the duo is taken on a wild ride from the Big Apple to Louisiana's Bayou Country. A pulpy tale of crime, full of snappy dialogue, twists and turns, and the unraveling mysteries of the past.
name: John Lord

description:
English translation of the Japanese manga Orochi (おろち).

From the "master of horror manga" (Asia Pulp Cinema) comes another super graphic novel. Orochi: Blood is a tale of two sisters: Kazusa, the older, perfect sister, and Lisa, her supposed inferior. Following a car accident, Lisa is saved by a girl named Orochi, who then mysteriously falls asleep for several decades. When Orochi awakens, she's being taken to a mansion where the two women live. Lisa is now caring for the ill Kazusa. What strange secret binds the sisters to each other, and Orochi to both of them?
name: Orochi: Blood
